blog.title: alt.ravenclaw.nerd.nerd.nerd
blog.description:
✧ My ask box is usually off. To get in touch with me, @mention me in a post or post something tagged #silveth. It's OK to message me if I follow you, but don't expect immediate responses. That little message notification balloon often makes me anxious and I have to work up to clicking on it. (ya rly.) I rarely follow back people who follow me without there having been some prior contact between us (not never, but not often). I run off a queue of 3-4 posts a day pretty much 24/7. ✧

✧ I'm 40, cis female, Californian (sitting on Ohlone land), Pagan, fae/sidhe, nerd, library cataloger, ISTJ, Virgo liek woah. Be warned: I am introverted, sarcastic, and not very good at looking like a beautiful, kind, interesting person 'cause, yanno, I am really not one. I am usually known in fandom contexts as shyfoxling. ✧

✧ Expect a lot of David Tennant because he is all the awesome. Other contents include, but are not limited to: mythic stuff, Paganism, Doctor Who, Harry Potter (pro-Snape), Tolkien, other nerdy fandom stuff, trees, the stars, occasional American politics and society, and general silliness. If you want otherkin content, you want my sideblog @arethinn. ✧

✧ Rah rah Ravenclaw! ✧

blog.name: 9or10allgood
blog.title: Winter Storm Warning...
blog.description:
Just a hair older than middle-aged, mother, transplanted Georgian living in Texas. I love my son more than my life. I'm a bit of a nerd - Whovian since forever. I would say I'm in love with David Tennant but a woman my age should be beyond such shenanigans. Or so I've been told.

Also a fan of NCIS, NCIS:Los Angeles, Star Trek (in all its permutations), Top Gear UK (before the *ahem* dust up) and The Grand Tour, The Big Bang Theory, and The West Wing.

Also, The Wheel of Time. The Dragon Rides the Winds of Time - Forever.

Politically moderate, socially liberal, spiritual, sarcastic. Frustrated inventor, meteorologist wannabe. And I would go to space in a heartbeat.

Anti-Trump - now and always.

On the subject of Doctor Who and Moffat, think of me as Switzerland. Determined to remain neutral. Open to the good, acknowledging the bad, not willing to fight about it.

Have some chocolate. ;)

summary: I’ve been thinking too much about this, and because I doubt the video will ever be available, all I have are my thoughts. And I...
body:
I’ve been thinking too much about this, and because I doubt the video will ever be available, all I have are my thoughts. And I have a lot of them.

During read throughs and rehearsals, Beatrice and Benedick put quite an exclamation point on their declarations. This development went as far as an audience. I wonder for how long this version of the production went on for, and what made them change it so their first kiss happened at the end of the show.

It does follow the Branagh 1992 film where they kiss after “I love you with so much of my heart…” confession, and I’ll be honest, it’s a sweet moment in the film. The 2011 production takes a more comedic approach that works perfectly for the stage.

To go back to what made them change it. I’m intrigued/curious about that conversation. Someone must have said it would be more impactful if their first kiss was at the end, in front of everyone, a pay off of not just the show but of years of UST building up.

Now I’m wondering what kind of kiss this was at this moment. From the screenshot, it looks rather passionate (like it would be anything else with those two). Was it joyful? Laughing? Did they beam and smile after it was over? Did they react as they do in the filmed production (shocked at how amazing it was)?  It makes “Kill Claudio” all the more impactful if it comes right after such a romantic/sexy exchange. Don’t get me wrong: “Kill Claudio” is impactful just the way it is in the 2011 production. It pulls the run out from them, and it would have been the same, yet different if she’d said it after they kissed.

Or was it a blooper? In that case, my mind will spin in an entirely different direction that’s just pure adorableness.

My mind is spinning about it in a way it hasn’t in a while. It’s fun and I’m going to continue to enjoy the ride.
